trans-unit.source: Data Factory Developer Reference
trans-unit.target: Data Factory Developer Reference

trans-unit.source: Azure Data Factory is a managed service that you can use to produce trusted information from raw data in cloud or on-premises data sources.
trans-unit.target: Azure Data Factory is a managed service that you can use to produce trusted information from raw data in cloud or on-premises data sources.

trans-unit.source: It allows developers to build data-driven workflows (pipelines) that join, aggregate and transform data sourced from their local, cloud-based and internet services, and set up complex data processing logic with little programming.
trans-unit.target: It allows developers to build data-driven workflows (pipelines) that join, aggregate and transform data sourced from their local, cloud-based and internet services, and set up complex data processing logic with little programming.

trans-unit.source: The Azure Data Factory service enables the easy monitoring and management of these pipelines by providing rich visual experience offered through Azure Portal.
trans-unit.target: The Azure Data Factory service enables the easy monitoring and management of these pipelines by providing rich visual experience offered through Azure Portal.

trans-unit.source: The information produced by pipelines can be easily consumed from BI, analytics tools, and other applications to reliably drive key business insights and decisions.
trans-unit.target: The information produced by pipelines can be easily consumed from BI, analytics tools, and other applications to reliably drive key business insights and decisions.

trans-unit.source: See <externalLink><linkText>Azure Data Factory conceptual content</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=516909</linkUri></externalLink> for more details.
trans-unit.target: See <externalLink><linkText>Azure Data Factory conceptual content</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=516909</linkUri></externalLink> for more details.

trans-unit.source: PowerShell Cmdlet Reference
trans-unit.target: PowerShell Cmdlet Reference

trans-unit.source: You can use Azure PowerShell cmdlets to create, monitor, manage, and troubleshoot Azure data factories.
trans-unit.target: You can use Azure PowerShell cmdlets to create, monitor, manage, and troubleshoot Azure data factories.

trans-unit.source: JSON Scripting Reference
trans-unit.target: JSON Scripting Reference

trans-unit.source: You need to create JSON files and use them with Azure PowerShell cmdlets to create pipelines, linked services and tables.
trans-unit.target: You need to create JSON files and use them with Azure PowerShell cmdlets to create pipelines, linked services and tables.

trans-unit.source: See <link xlink:href="ce650a59-105e-40bb-8f7b-ca59438276ca" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Data Factory JSON Scripting Reference</link> for syntax and examples for defining pipelines, linked services, and tables in JSON files.

trans-unit.source: Functions Reference
trans-unit.target: Functions Reference

trans-unit.source: Azure Data Factory functions allow you to specify values for string properties in a JSON file at runtime.
trans-unit.target: Azure Data Factory functions allow you to specify values for string properties in a JSON file at runtime.

trans-unit.source: When you assign the output of a Data Factory function to a string property in a JSON file, the function is evaluated at runtime and the output value will be assigned to the string property.
trans-unit.target: When you assign the output of a Data Factory function to a string property in a JSON file, the function is evaluated at runtime and the output value will be assigned to the string property.

trans-unit.source: See <link xlink:href="ce76160a-90f2-4459-950a-34c43d8c919b" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Data Factory Functions</link> for details.
